The South Africans were quarantined at the Ranch Resort outside Polokwane. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced yesterday the students, management of the hotel and the army, which evacuated the students from China, have all tested negative for the virus and declared the hotel a green zone. The ANC Youth League (ANCYL) in the Peter Mokaba region, where the hotel used for quarantine is situated, initially threatened to plunge the province into turmoil. But the league’s threats evaporated after the ANC, led by Health Minister Zweli Mkhize, gave them a tongue-lashing. “We are now more united than ever because the ANC in...